-default\">FAQs on Goa<\/h4>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-4875cb5 elementor-widget elementor-widget-elementskit-faq\" data-id=\"4875cb5\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"elementskit-faq.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"ekit-wid-con\" >\n                <div class=\"elementskit-single-faq elementor-repeater-item-7afa21a\">\n            <div class=\"elementskit-faq-header\">\n                <h2 class=\"elementskit-faq-title\">1. What is the best time to visit Goa?<\/h2>\n            <\/div>\n            <div class=\"elementskit-faq-body\">\n                The ideal time is between November and February, when the weather is pleasant (20 \u00b0C to 30 \u00b0C), skies are clear, and outdoor activities are enjoyable. \n            <\/div>\n        <\/div>\n                <div class=\"elementskit-single-faq elementor-repeater-item-6e357a8\">\n            <div class=\"elementskit-faq-header\">\n                <h2 class=\"elementskit-faq-title\">2. What are the top beaches to visit in Goa?<\/h2>\n            <\/div>\n            <div class=\"elementskit-faq-body\">\n                Some of the must-visit beaches include:\n\nCalangute Beach (largest &amp; popular) \n\nBaga Beach (nightlife, water sports) \n\n\nPalolem Beach (serene, scenic in South Goa) \n\n\nArambol Beach (boho, offbeat vibes)            <\/div>\n        <\/div>\n                <div class=\"elementskit-single-faq elementor-repeater-item-a7f8776\">\n            <div class=\"elementskit-faq-header\">\n                <h2 class=\"elementskit-faq-title\">3. What activities can I do in Goa?<\/h2>\n            <\/div>\n            <div class=\"elementskit-faq-body\">\n                You can enjoy:\n\nWater sports (jet-skiing, parasailing, scuba diving, windsurfing) \n\n\nRiver cruises (e.g. Mandovi River sunset cruise) \n\nNightlife: beach shacks, nightclubs, casinos, music festivals \n\n\nCultural &amp; heritage tours: churches, forts, local museums \n\n\nNature and wildlife: sanctuaries, backwaters, waterfalls, trekking            <\/div>\n        <\/div>\n                <div class=\"elementskit-single-faq elementor-repeater-item-7ec4103\">\n            <div class=\"elementskit-faq-header\">\n                <h2 class=\"elementskit-faq-title\">4. Which heritage sites should I visit in Goa?<\/h2>\n            <\/div>\n            <div class=\"elementskit-faq-body\">\n                Some notable heritage and historic sites are:\n\nBasilica of Bom Jesus (UNESCO World Heritage) \n\nSe Cathedral \n\nFort Aguada \n\nChapora Fort \n\nReis Magos Fort            <\/div>\n        <\/div>\n                <div class=\"elementskit-single-faq elementor-repeater-item-9d58410\">\n            <div class=\"elementskit-faq-header\">\n                <h2 class=\"elementskit-faq-title\">5. How do I reach Dudhsagar Waterfalls?<\/h2>\n            <\/div>\n            <div class=\"elementskit-faq-body\">\n                The falls are located on the Goa\u2013Karnataka border and can be accessed via a scenic train ride or through a jeep safari inside the Bhagwan Mahavir Wildlife Sanctuary.            <\/div>\n        <\/div>\n                <div class=\"elementskit-single-faq elementor-repeater-item-e4ee8e0\">\n            <div class=\"elementskit-faq-header\">\n                <h2 class=\"elementskit-faq-title\">6. Are there wildlife or nature sanctuaries to visit?<\/h2>\n            <\/div>\n            <div class=\"elementskit-faq-body\">\n                Yes \u2014 for example:\n\nBhagwan Mahavir Wildlife Sanctuary (includes Tambdi Surla Temple)\nSalim Ali Bird Sanctuary on Chorao Island (mangrove &amp; birdlife)            <\/div>\n        <\/div>\n                <div class=\"elementskit-single-faq elementor-repeater-item-212766b\">\n            <div class=\"elementskit-faq-header\">\n                <h2 class=\"elementskit-faq-title\">7. What markets should I visit in Goa?<\/h2>\n            <\/div>\n            <div class=\"elementskit-faq-body\">\n                Anjuna Flea Market (every Wednesday)\nMapusa Friday Market (local life, handicrafts, spices)\nFontainhas Latin Quarter in Panaji (heritage walking &amp; boutique shops)            <\/div>\n        <\/div>\n                <div class=\"elementskit-single-faq elementor-repeater-item-289689d\">\n            <div class=\"elementskit-faq-header\">\n                <h2 class=\"elementskit-faq-title\">8. Is it possible to book customized tours for Goa?<\/h2>\n            <\/div>\n            <div class=\"elementskit-faq-body\">\n                Yes \u2014 Manu Adventures provides destination-expert support and handles customized queries. See the \u201cGot a Question?\u201d section.            <\/div>\n        <\/div>\n                <div class=\"elementskit-single-faq elementor-repeater-item-a564e6e\">\n            <div class=\"elementskit-faq-header\">\n                <h2 class=\"elementskit-faq-title\">9. How can I contact a Goa destination expert for queries?<\/h2>\n            <\/div>\n            <div class=\"elementskit-faq-body\">\n                Phone: +91-9736871426\nEmail: manuadventures@gmail.com\n\nAvailable 10:30 AM \u2013 8:00 PM (Monday to Saturday)            <\/div>\n        <\/div>\n                \n    <\/div>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-b198dfb elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"b198dfb\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h6 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Gallery<\/h6>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-7beeef0 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"7beeef0\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-con